description:
At GoBolt, we provide a technology-driven, customer-centric and sustainable approach to ecommerce and last-mile logistics for businesses of all sizes – from local brands to large national retailers. By operating as an extension of our customer's team, we deliver best-in-class services every step of the way.



We're building North America’s largest electric vehicle fleet to help bring sustainability to an industry notorious for its heavy impact on the environment. We are in high growth mode and building for the future, which is where you come in!



We are on the lookout for a **Transportation Team Lead** who shares our passion for being Customer Obsessed. In this dynamic role, you will play a crucial part in being responsible for overseeing daily warehouse operations, ensuring efficient and effective receipt, storage, and dispatch of a wide range of goods. This role involves leading a team of warehouse associates, coordinating activities, and maintaining high standards of safety, quality, and productivity. The ideal candidate will have strong leadership skills, a background in logistics or warehouse management, and the ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment. The ideal candidate is also ready to be apart of the process and is ready to get their hands dirty!

 **Shift Timing :**


**2pm - 10:30pm Friday to Tuesday**



**Key Responsibilities:**



* Receiving and storing inventory delivered to the warehouse;
* Staging and sorting of items, palletizing, and crating;
* Provide regular reports on warehouse performance and key metrics (SLAs) to the operations leadership,
* Move, pick, pack, and scan items in a safe manner;
* Use of tools including but not limited to scanners, carts, hand trucks and dollies;
* Daily submission and completion of all required documentation in an accurate fashion;
* Follow all 5S processes consistently and effectively;
* Create an inspiring team environment with an open communication culture;
* Train new employees on company standards and procedures;
* Lead, mentor, and supervise a team of warehouse associates;
* Assign tasks and responsibilities, ensuring efficient workflow and productivity;
* Conduct regular team meetings to communicate goals, updates, and feedback;
* Ensure accurate inventory management, including stock counts and reconciliations;
* Implement and maintain warehouse processes and procedures to maximize efficiency;
* Enforce safety standards and protocols to ensure a safe working environment;
* Address and resolve any issues related to damaged or missing goods;
* Liaise with other departments, such as procurement, account management, and customer service, to coordinate activities and resolve issues;
* Communicate effectively with team members, management, and external partners.




**Qualifications:**


* High school diploma or equivalent; bachelor's degree in logistics, supply chain management, or related field preferred;
* Proven experience in a warehouse or logistics role, with at least 2 years in a supervisory or team lead position;
* Strong leadership and team management skills;
* Excellent organizational and time-management abilities;
* Proficient in warehouse management software and the Google Suite;
* Knowledge of safety regulations and best practices in warehouse operations;
* Strong communication and interpersonal skills;
* Ability to work in a fast-paced and dynamic environment.




**Physical Requirements:**


* Ability to lift and carry heavy items (up to 50 lbs);
* Prolonged periods of standing and walking;
* Have a valid forklift license




**Why Join Us?**



We are innovative, goal-oriented, and are always on the search for energetic and passionate people who are eager to learn and would like to have a rare opportunity to grow within one of Canada's fastest-growing companies.



We offer a workplace where respect, diversity, and inclusion are the cornerstones of our culture. Our team members are encouraged to bring their authentic selves to work, contributing to our collective mission in their unique ways. Aside from an amazing culture, we also offer competitive salaries and a comprehensive benefits package including health, dental, and vision plans for you and your family.



If you are eager to make a difference and contribute to an exciting, fast-paced environment, we would love to hear from you.



GoBolt is an equal-opportunity employer that recognizes the value and importance of a diverse workforce. GoBolt is committed to providing assistance during all phases of the employment cycle, including recruiting through to the end of the employment relationship. If you require accommodation because of injury, illness, or disability during any portion of GoBolt’s recruiting process, please let us know by contacting your recruiter's point of contact, and we will do everything we can to accommodate you.

